  "response": "Not all smartphones have Bluetooth 4.0 or BLE (Bluetooth Low Energy). While most modern smartphones support these technologies, older models may not. Bluetooth 4.0, which introduced BLE, was released in 2010, so smartphones manufactured before this may not support it. Additionally, entry-level or budget smartphones may also lack BLE support, depending on their hardware specifications and the manufacturer's choices. Always check the specific model's specifications to confirm its Bluetooth capabilities.",
